	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />All,
<br />
<br />I have a Toaster NES hooked up via composite to an older 32" Sharp 720p LCD.  When using my NES Powerpak, I get wavy lines on the screen.  None of my other carts produce these wavy lines though.
<br />
<br />I tried on 3 different TVs.  Same issue exists on all.
<br />
<br /><a href="http://nintendoage.com/media/_usermedia/attachments/DSCF3479%2EJPG" class="postlink">PIC1</a>:  Powerpak playing SMB.  These lines wave back and forth and go up and down the screen.
<br />
<br /><a href="http://nintendoage.com/media/_usermedia/attachments/DSCF3482%2EJPG" class="postlink">PIC2</a>:  Vs SMB cart from retrozone.  Notice, no wavy lines.
<br />
<br />I'll be borrowing a NES console and powerbrick from a friend tomorrow to try.
<br />
<br />Anyone have any ideas of what could be causing the Powerpak to do so?  Is it some sort of interference caused by the Powerpak?  Any other thoughts?
<br />
<br />Any help is greatly appreciated! 
<br />
<br />Thanks
<br />
<br />EDIT:  Before anyone asks, yes my NES has the shielding and I am using an offical NES-002 AC Adaptor.  Thanks

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


